definitions.definition: An enclosure from which water can be expelled , in order to give access to underwater areas for engineering works etc.
The gate across the entrance to a dry dock .
A floating tank that can be submerged , attached to an underwater object and then pumped out to lift the object by buoyancy ; a camel .
A two-wheeled, horse-drawn military vehicle used to carry ammunition (and a coffin at funerals ).
A large box to hold ammunition.
A chest filled with explosive materials, used like a mine .

main_definition: ( engineering ) An enclosure from which water can be expelled , in order to give access to underwater areas for engineering works etc.

( military ) A large box to hold ammunition.
( military ) A chest filled with explosive materials, used like a mine .
